===Adverb===
{{en-adv}}
# In a [[yielding]] way.
#* '''1934''', {{w|George Orwell}}, ''{{w|Burmese Days}}'', New York: Harcourt, 1974, Chapter 14, p. 168,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/burmesedaysnovel00orwe]</sup>
#*: A sudden stillness came on them both, a sense of something momentous that must happen.  Flory reached across and took her other hand.  It came '''yieldingly''', willingly.
#* '''1974''', {{w|Angela Carter}}, “The Smile of Winter” in ''{{w|Fireworks: Nine Profane Pieces|Fireworks}}'', London: Virago, 1988, p. 44,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/fireworksviragom00ange]</sup>
#*: The wet sand is as dark and more '''yieldingly''' solid than fudge and waking across a panful is a promenade in the Kingdom of Sweets.
